	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: RGB output from composite PPU</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The NES generates a 240p signal, and I'd imagine that a lot of TVs with component input can't handle 240p component input, only 480i, 480p, 720p, and 1080i, and 1080p. My Vizio VX32L, for example, produces a distorted picture when I play PlayStation games on my slim PS2 or <em>Mega Man X Collection</em> on my Wii unless I switch to the composite cable.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


